{
  "local_port": 40372,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "Configuring your TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) email on an iPhone involves setting up your email account using either the **Exchange** or **IMAP** protocols, depending on how your organization's email system is configured. Below are step-by-step instructions for both methods. It's advisable to check with your IT department for specific settings related to your organization.\n\n### **Method 1: Using Exchange**\n\nIf TCS uses a Microsoft Exchange server for email, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Settings:**\n   - Tap the **Settings** app on your iPhone\u2019s home screen.\n\n2. **Navigate to Accounts:**\n   - Scroll down and select **Mail**.\n   - Tap on **Accounts**.\n   \n3. **Add Account:**\n   - Tap **Add Account**.\n   - From the list of email providers, select **Microsoft Exchange**.\n\n4. **Enter Email Information:**\n   - **Email:** Enter your full TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com).\n   - **Description:** Enter a description for the account (e.g., \"TCS Email\").\n   - Tap **Next**.\n\n5. **Sign In to Exchange:**\n   - You may be prompted to sign in using your TCS credentials. Follow the on-screen instructions.\n   - If your organization uses Office 365 or has specific server settings, you may need to enter them manually. If so, toggle **\"Sign In\"** to off and enter the following details:\n     - **Email:** Your full TCS email address.\n     - **Server:** (e.g., `outlook.office365.com` or your organization's Exchange server address).\n     - **Domain:** Often left blank or filled with your organization's domain (e.g., `tcs.com`).\n     - **Username:** Your full email address or as specified by your IT department.\n     - **Password:** Your email password.\n   \n6. **Choose Data to Sync:**\n   - After successfully signing in, you can choose which data to sync (Mail, Contacts, Calendars, Reminders, Notes).\n   - Toggle the switches according to your preference.\n   \n7. **Save:**\n   - Tap **Save** to complete the setup.\n\n### **Method 2: Using IMAP**\n\nIf TCS uses an IMAP server for email, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Settings:**\n   - Tap the **Settings** app on your iPhone\u2019s home screen.\n\n2. **Navigate to Accounts:**\n   - Scroll down and select **Mail**.\n   - Tap on **Accounts**.\n\n3. **Add Account:**\n   - Tap **Add Account**.\n   - Scroll down and select **Other**.\n\n4. **Add Mail Account:**\n   - Tap **Add Mail Account**.\n   \n5. **Enter Account Information:**\n   - **Name:** Your full name as you want it to appear in outgoing emails.\n   - **Email:** Your full TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com).\n   - **Password:** Your email password.\n   - **Description:** Enter a description for the account (e.g., \"TCS IMAP Email\").\n   - Tap **Next**.\n\n6. **Configure Incoming Mail Server:**\n   - **Host Name:** Enter your IMAP server address (e.g., `imap.tcs.com`).\n   - **User Name:** Your full email address or as specified by your IT department.\n   - **Password:** Your email password.\n\n7. **Configure Outgoing Mail Server:**\n   - **Host Name:** Enter your SMTP server address (e.g., `smtp.tcs.com`).\n   - **User Name:** Your full email address or as specified by your IT department.\n   - **Password:** Your email password.\n   \n8. **Advanced Settings (if required):**\n   - Tap on your email account under **Accounts** > **Your Email Account** > **Account**.\n   - Scroll down to **Incoming Settings** and **Outgoing Settings** to ensure that:\n     - **Use SSL** is enabled.\n     - **Authentication** is set to **Password**.\n     - The correct **Server Port** is entered (commonly 993 for IMAP and 587 or 465 for SMTP).\n   \n9. **Save:**\n   - After entering all required information, tap **Save** to complete the setup.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Server Information:** If you're unsure about the server settings (IMAP/SMTP addresses, ports, etc.), contact your TCS IT support or refer to internal documentation.\n  \n- **Security:** Ensure that SSL is enabled for both incoming and outgoing servers to secure your email communication.\n  \n- **Multiple Accounts:** If you have multiple email accounts, repeat the above steps for each account, choosing the appropriate method (Exchange or IMAP) based on your organization's configuration.\n\n- **Sync Settings:** After setting up, you can customize how much data you want to sync (e.g., Mail Days to Sync) in the account settings to optimize performance.\n\n### **Troubleshooting:**\n\n- **Incorrect Password:** Ensure that the password entered is correct. If you've recently changed your password, use the updated one.\n  \n- **Server Errors:** Double-check the server addresses and port numbers. Incorrect settings can prevent successful configuration.\n  \n- **Contact IT Support:** If you encounter persistent issues, reach out to your organization's IT support team for assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully configure your TCS email account on your iPhone. Always ensure you have the necessary permissions and information from your IT department before making changes to your email settings.",
